FT  12 AUG 94 / World News in Brief: Horror film actor Peter Cushing dies
Actor Peter Cushing, star of 22 Hammer horror films, died yesterday, aged
81. Cushing, pictured left as Sherlock Holmes in The Hound of the
Baskervilles, was best known for films such as The Curse of Frankenstein,
The Mummy, and Dracula, in which he was often teamed with Christopher Lee.
He made many other films, worked on the stage and for television, and was
awarded an OBE in 1989.
